#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
pseudo_voynich.py — Synthetic Pseudo-Voynich Generator  [v2 — Phytoglyphica Edition]

Generates synthetic Voynich text that has ZERO surface resemblance to the
Voynich Manuscript (Shavian notation instead of EVA) while reproducing every
measurable statistical property that defines the Voynich corpus.

NEW IN v2 (Phytoglyphica-perfected):
  - Full 30-glyph EVA inventory with frequency-preserving mapping
  - Dual output: --mode eva (original EVA glyphs) or --mode shavian (default)
  - Six-section model: botanical, astronomical, cosmological, pharmaceutical,
    balneological, biological/recipe — matching Voynich_Phytoglyphica §Engine
  - Semantic synthesis: --herbs N generates botanical monographs with
    pharmaceutical metadata derived from the 1,491-entry phytoglyphica catalog
  - Recipe synthesis: --recipes N generates procedural recipe entries matching
    the 1,076-entry phytoglyphica recipe corpus
  - Section boundaries from actual Voynich folio ranges (f1–f66 botanical, etc.)
  - Bigram matrix over ALL glyphs (not just 12-primitive subset)

Statistical signatures matched:
  word-length distribution, Zipf exponent, bigram (conditional) entropy,
  positional token constraints, section vocabulary separation (KL),
  type-token ratio, local word-repetition anomaly, spectral gap

Usage:
    python pseudo_voynich.py PATH/TO/LSI_ivtff_0d.txt
    python pseudo_voynich.py PATH/TO/LSI_ivtff_0d.txt --section botanical --lines 200
    python pseudo_voynich.py PATH/TO/LSI_ivtff_0d.txt --stats-only
    python pseudo_voynich.py PATH/TO/LSI_ivtff_0d.txt --output synth.txt
    python pseudo_voynich.py PATH/TO/LSI_ivtff_0d.txt --mode eva
    python pseudo_voynich.py PATH/TO/LSI_ivtff_0d.txt --herbs 50
    python pseudo_voynich.py PATH/TO/LSI_ivtff_0d.txt --recipes 100
"""

